kinhou12/22/23
The Karemian Federation, former colony of the IAE, fought ferociously in the First Continental War, a war that engulfed the entirety of the Karemian continent into a war for liberation.

Both North and South Karemi achieved their independence, creating multiple new nation states from the ashes of the old colonial empire.

However, there was much work to do, as the war had only ended 3 years prior, the Karemian Federation was in a dire situation, as well as the multiple states that had been freed in North Karemi.

The first President of the Federal States of Karemi had a vision for the continent, a vision of a United Front in North Karemi that would allow all of the continent to stand up against the tyranny of the Leuknizian continents.

Now, filled with the determination to Realize their Destiny, the Federal States would rise up like a powerful Phoenix from the ashes of liberation and freedom. Like the warriors they are.
